headline: Tyler Technologies beats quarterly revenue estimates on strong demand for IT services
summary: Tyler Technologies surpassed Wall Street's fourth-quarter revenue expectations, driven by strong demand for its IT services. The shift of clients from on-premises data systems to cloud-based solutions, along with the company's expansion into new markets, are key drivers of Tyler Technologies' revenue growth. Tyler Technologies posted revenue of $541.1 million for the quarter ended December 31, beating analysts' average estimate of $540.5 million, according to data compiled by LSEG data.
